WEBVTT

00:02.069 --> 00:03.536
J:
This diamond guy paid 80 grand
for those, just like that.

00:03.538 --> 00:04.737
Deran: The brother knew
that the shit was cut.

00:04.739 --> 00:06.005
There's something off
between the two of them.

00:06.007 --> 00:07.673
I think we could use it.
-Hey, Arthur.

00:07.675 --> 00:09.008
I wanna rip off
your brother.

00:09.010 --> 00:10.876
Do you know
who Brock Fellows is?

00:10.878 --> 00:12.745
He's throwing a birthday party
for his girlfriend in two weeks,

00:12.747 --> 00:15.080
and he's renting a few
of Eddie's favorite pieces.

00:15.082 --> 00:16.615
I've been doing
some research.

00:16.617 --> 00:18.751
I think we should look into
setting up a trust.

00:18.753 --> 00:20.553
Sitting on money
is wasting money.

00:20.555 --> 00:22.755
Man:
I didn't ask for you to be
assigned to my cold-case unit.

00:22.757 --> 00:24.223
Me neither.
So, what do you got?

00:24.225 --> 00:26.759
Tell me what you remember
about that last day, Lena.

00:26.761 --> 00:28.694
You saw your mom
and dad together, right?

00:28.696 --> 00:30.563
Lena: Uncle Pope
was there, too.

00:30.565 --> 00:32.565
Everything okay?

00:32.567 --> 00:33.966
Some business shit.

00:33.968 --> 00:35.701
Other ways
of making a living.

00:35.703 --> 00:37.502
All I'm saying is, it don't
have to be with your family.

00:37.504 --> 00:40.573
Smurf:
I've got a lead on a job,
and I want<i> all</i> of us to do it.

00:40.575 --> 00:42.174
-What is it?
-The rectory.

00:42.176 --> 00:44.509
-No.
-We need the money.

00:44.511 --> 00:45.911
Just let me skate!

00:45.913 --> 00:48.447
You pick up the board
and swing it, or you get out.

00:48.449 --> 00:49.715
-You want some?!
-Bro, chill.

00:49.717 --> 00:51.584
How much longer
I gotta do this?

00:51.586 --> 00:53.686
As long as
I need you to.

00:56.924 --> 00:59.725
♪♪

00:59.727 --> 01:05.664
♪ She stares deeply ♪

01:05.666 --> 01:09.402
♪ Locked inside me ♪

01:09.404 --> 01:12.605
♪ Burnin' brightly ♪

01:15.410 --> 01:21.080
♪ One they know
that I cannot take ♪

01:21.082 --> 01:24.683
♪ Waitin' for it all to begin ♪

01:24.685 --> 01:27.854
♪ Every night now, they'll win ♪

01:31.692 --> 01:34.359
♪ Come and meet my black hole ♪

01:34.361 --> 01:38.231
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:38.233 --> 01:42.101
♪ Got a big black hole ♪

01:42.103 --> 01:45.838
♪ I've got a big black hole ♪

01:45.840 --> 01:49.975
♪ I've got a big black,
big black hole ♪

01:49.977 --> 01:53.979
♪ Got a big black hole
inside of me ♪

01:53.981 --> 01:55.948
♪ Got a ♪

02:01.588 --> 02:04.123
J: There's one.

02:04.125 --> 02:07.192
Deran: No.
It's got to be red.

02:07.194 --> 02:08.927
We don't have enough time
to paint the whole thing.

02:08.929 --> 02:10.263
Yeah, that's
'cause Logan's slow.

02:10.265 --> 02:11.797
We should have used Mark.

02:11.799 --> 02:13.799
Yeah, well, Mark married
some rich girl.

02:13.801 --> 02:15.535
He lives in Del Mar now.

02:21.876 --> 02:24.343
You alright?

02:24.345 --> 02:27.280
Yeah.

02:27.282 --> 02:28.981
Some shit with Craig.

02:31.352 --> 02:36.955
He's got some sponsor down
in Escondido, some biker dude.

02:36.957 --> 02:40.293
It seems like
it's working.

02:40.295 --> 02:42.561
Yeah, well, when he left the
family meeting the other day,

02:42.563 --> 02:44.429
he told me
he was going to the gym,

02:44.431 --> 02:46.565
but I found him
at the garage.

02:46.567 --> 02:48.701
Didn't exactly look like
an AA meeting.

02:48.703 --> 02:51.470
Is it something we're gonna
have to worry about?

02:52.640 --> 02:58.443
♪♪

02:58.445 --> 03:03.849
♪♪

03:03.851 --> 03:05.450
Vince, grab the door.

03:05.452 --> 03:08.721
♪♪

03:08.723 --> 03:10.455
[ Grunts ]

03:10.457 --> 03:17.730
♪♪

03:17.732 --> 03:20.600
Wait.
[ Crashes ]

03:21.068 --> 03:25.938
♪♪

03:25.940 --> 03:27.540
Yo, I thought you said
they were at the bar.

03:27.542 --> 03:29.875
Hey! You broke into
the wrong rig, asshole.

03:29.877 --> 03:32.077
Let's go.
Son of a --

03:32.079 --> 03:36.415
[ Grunting ]

03:36.417 --> 03:37.816
Hey!

03:37.818 --> 03:39.752
Who are you?
He still owes me $40.

03:39.754 --> 03:42.421
Take it and go.
Let's move! Let's go!

03:42.423 --> 03:46.825
♪♪

03:46.827 --> 03:48.493
Hey, yo, we good.
We good?

03:48.495 --> 03:49.895
Yeah.
Stay there.

03:49.897 --> 03:51.630
[ Crowbar clatters ]

03:51.632 --> 04:01.040
♪♪

04:01.042 --> 04:04.309
Smurf: Your breakfast
is getting cold, baby.

04:04.311 --> 04:09.514
You can't go on a job
with an empty stomach.

04:09.516 --> 04:11.150
I'm not hungry.

04:14.722 --> 04:17.189
[ Exhales sharply ]

04:17.191 --> 04:19.625
I know you think
I don't understand.

04:21.996 --> 04:27.133
But you meeting this priest
was a good thing.

04:29.204 --> 04:32.238
I didn't know where we were
gonna find our next job.

04:34.475 --> 04:41.346
And then he just
magically appeared.

04:41.348 --> 04:45.150
Isn't there something
for that in the Bible?

04:45.152 --> 04:47.152
Fate?

04:47.154 --> 04:49.554
Destiny?

04:49.556 --> 04:51.290
It's not fate.

04:51.292 --> 04:55.560
Oh, you call it
whatever you want.

04:55.562 --> 04:57.696
It's meant to be.

04:57.698 --> 05:02.101
Hey.
Ready?

05:02.103 --> 05:03.302
Of course he is.

05:03.304 --> 05:05.938
The service gets out
at noon, right?

05:08.042 --> 05:10.709
Babe.

05:10.711 --> 05:20.319
♪♪

05:20.321 --> 05:22.387
[ Water running, splashing ]

05:22.389 --> 05:26.259
[ Both panting, moaning ]

05:26.261 --> 05:31.130
♪♪

05:31.132 --> 05:32.865
What?

05:32.867 --> 05:36.068
I've already been
late to work.
So?

05:36.070 --> 05:39.538
So, if you want everything ready
for<i> your</i> meeting today,

05:39.540 --> 05:44.143
then you're gonna want me
in the office on time.

05:44.145 --> 05:45.678
If you wanted
more time with me,

05:45.680 --> 05:48.614
you should have texted
before 2:00 am.

05:48.616 --> 05:51.617
Are you mad that I did?

05:51.619 --> 05:53.252
No.

06:00.094 --> 06:03.428
This place is nice.
Thanks.

06:03.430 --> 06:06.231
You, uh, still making
payments on it?

06:06.233 --> 06:08.501
No. My grandma paid it off
a long time ago.

06:08.503 --> 06:10.769
Good for her.

06:10.771 --> 06:12.905
I'd kill for
a house like this.

06:12.907 --> 06:14.707
You'll get one.

06:14.709 --> 06:17.776
Just give your parking lot
a few years.

06:17.778 --> 06:19.378
Yeah.

06:22.517 --> 06:24.783
[ Chuckles ]

06:24.785 --> 06:26.785
Mm.
I should get home.

06:26.787 --> 06:30.255
Go change, skip the walk
of shame this time.

06:30.257 --> 06:36.461
♪♪

06:36.463 --> 06:38.531
I'll see you
later, okay?

06:38.533 --> 06:40.666
Alright.

06:40.668 --> 06:47.940
♪♪

06:47.942 --> 06:49.474
Man: Alright, guys.

06:49.476 --> 06:51.076
Whoa,
watch out, man!

06:51.078 --> 06:53.679
Hey, out of the drive path.

06:53.681 --> 07:00.019
You know the rules.

07:00.021 --> 07:03.022
Boy.
Eh, don't sweat it,
Felix.

07:03.024 --> 07:04.890
Thinks he's still a cop.

07:04.892 --> 07:06.759
Yeah, what'd you do
to your hand?

07:06.761 --> 07:09.962
Eh, it's nothing, man.

07:09.964 --> 07:11.430
I saw you around,
uh, yesterday.

07:11.432 --> 07:12.765
You new?
Yeah.

07:12.767 --> 07:13.966
Just giving it a shot.

07:13.968 --> 07:15.768
I need a quick buck,
you know?

07:15.770 --> 07:19.905
Alright.

07:19.907 --> 07:22.507
Alright.
Let's get something.

07:22.509 --> 07:23.709
-Alright, guys.
-Ooh!

07:23.711 --> 07:25.844
[ Camera shutters click ]

07:25.846 --> 07:27.747
No, it's nothing.

07:31.386 --> 07:34.053
Been this party bullshit
for days.

07:34.055 --> 07:35.854
Yeah, man, it looks like
it's gonna be a big deal.

07:35.856 --> 07:37.856
Hey, shades,
off the property.

07:37.858 --> 07:41.260
How many times I need
to say it, huh?

07:41.262 --> 07:44.463
Look, man,
has anyone, um --

07:44.465 --> 07:47.666
anyone ever just snuck in,
try to get a shot inside?

07:47.668 --> 07:50.870
Not me, but this one guy, uh,
snuck in on the back

07:50.872 --> 07:52.671
of the landscaping
truck last year.

07:52.673 --> 07:54.407
Uh-huh.
He made it past the gate.

07:54.409 --> 07:56.942
And? What happened?
Did they call the cops?

07:56.944 --> 07:58.543
What happened?
[ Laughs ]

07:58.545 --> 08:01.814
Uh, you think Brock wants,
uh, LAPD showing up?

08:01.816 --> 08:03.416
Felix talked to him.

08:03.418 --> 08:04.950
Never saw him again.

08:04.952 --> 08:06.486
Oh, damn.

08:08.489 --> 08:12.825
[ Door shuts ]

08:12.827 --> 08:16.028
Wow.

08:16.030 --> 08:18.030
They look great.
Yeah.

08:18.032 --> 08:19.832
Arthur even got
the weight right.

08:19.834 --> 08:22.234
I mean, CZ's are heavier
than diamonds.

08:22.236 --> 08:23.502
He must've shaved
the backings.

08:23.504 --> 08:26.505
I'm telling you, man.
He knows what he's doing.

08:26.507 --> 08:28.908
Those new?
Mm-hmm.

08:28.910 --> 08:33.245
So, it looks like
LA sanitation redid

08:33.247 --> 08:34.780
all the plumbing
in Brock's neighborhood.

08:34.782 --> 08:39.118
I guess celebrities can't go
with a backed-up toilet.

08:39.120 --> 08:42.521
[ Buzzing ]

08:42.523 --> 08:45.390
[ Slam ]

08:45.392 --> 08:46.926
You gonna answer it?

08:46.928 --> 08:48.394
I'm gonna answer it later.

08:53.000 --> 08:55.200
Dude.

08:55.202 --> 08:57.937
Hey, dude, be careful.
It's not even real.

08:57.939 --> 09:01.073
Just --
Just be put it down, please.

09:01.075 --> 09:02.675
Okay.

09:02.677 --> 09:05.144
Just -- I got it.

09:05.146 --> 09:06.879
You got that iron?

09:06.881 --> 09:09.148
Uh, yeah, it's there.

09:09.150 --> 09:11.817
You don't own an iron?

09:11.819 --> 09:13.352
No, I don't own an iron.

09:19.827 --> 09:21.827
Just let me do it.

09:21.829 --> 09:24.363
Just give it to me.
What?

09:24.365 --> 09:26.499
Burn the house down
with that thing.

09:26.501 --> 09:33.038
♪♪

09:33.040 --> 09:39.645
♪♪

09:39.647 --> 09:43.648
Check this out.

09:43.650 --> 09:45.318
Found some cash in a bible.

09:48.189 --> 09:49.655
Damn.

09:49.657 --> 09:50.990
What?

09:50.992 --> 09:53.859
Who knew, preacher man's
a Zeppelin fan.

09:53.861 --> 09:55.394
Is that even allowed?

09:55.396 --> 09:59.198
♪♪

09:59.200 --> 10:02.801
Hey, be careful!

10:02.803 --> 10:04.670
Jackpot.

10:04.672 --> 10:08.941
Hey, grab the crowbar.

10:08.943 --> 10:11.476
-What are you doing?!
-Run!

10:11.478 --> 10:14.813
What are you doing?!

10:14.815 --> 10:21.086
Julia!
Get in the car!

10:21.088 --> 10:22.287
What the hell happened?

10:22.289 --> 10:24.023
Come on.
Just drive!

10:24.025 --> 10:27.026
Are you okay?
God damn it, Andrew!

10:27.028 --> 10:29.428
Who was that guy?

10:43.744 --> 10:48.814
[ Speaking indistinctly ]

10:48.816 --> 10:50.349
We're ready for you.

10:50.351 --> 10:54.486
We're just waiting on my uncle.
He's running a little late.

10:54.488 --> 10:56.288
Raj has back-to-back
meetings today,

10:56.290 --> 10:58.357
so if you want to
reschedule...?

10:58.359 --> 11:00.426
We just need
a few more minutes.

11:09.837 --> 11:12.771
Nice.
What? It's five minutes,
man. Relax.

11:12.773 --> 11:15.708
This everyone?
Yeah.

11:15.710 --> 11:17.043
Okay.

11:17.045 --> 11:24.516
♪♪

11:24.518 --> 11:32.058
♪♪

11:32.060 --> 11:33.659
Big day.

11:33.661 --> 11:36.929
Nice to finally meet everyone.

11:36.931 --> 11:39.331
Alright, if you want to open
up to page two,

11:39.333 --> 11:41.533
you'll find
your investment allocation

11:41.535 --> 11:43.736
as I discussed with Josh here.

11:43.738 --> 11:47.273
Yeah, we're all invested equally
in the funds we agreed on.

11:47.275 --> 11:50.542
So, uh...

11:50.544 --> 11:52.544
Did you read it?

11:52.546 --> 11:54.080
I skimmed it.

11:54.082 --> 11:57.215
We, uh, had our in-house notary
fill out her side of things.

11:57.217 --> 12:00.352
I have the paperwork right here.

12:00.354 --> 12:03.155
Or at least I should.
Pen?

12:03.157 --> 12:06.625
Didn't I ask for the notary
paperwork?

12:06.627 --> 12:08.294
It's on the left.

12:08.296 --> 12:09.895
Ah, okay.

12:09.897 --> 12:12.030
Are you guys thirsty?
Get these guys some waters.

12:12.032 --> 12:14.100
The family corporation
will be the trustee,

12:14.102 --> 12:16.903
so any changes need
everyone's approval.

12:16.905 --> 12:18.971
What? So we need to go
through all this shit again

12:18.973 --> 12:20.506
any time we want
to make another change?

12:20.508 --> 12:21.907
That's the deal.
Unless you want to pay me again.

12:21.909 --> 12:23.309
When will the, uh,
distributions start

12:23.311 --> 12:24.843
showing up
in our accounts?

12:24.845 --> 12:27.579
It should take a week
for everything to process.

12:27.581 --> 12:29.648
After that, you'll each receive
direct deposit

12:29.650 --> 12:31.450
quarterly dividends.

12:31.452 --> 12:33.185
How much?
It's up to you.

12:33.187 --> 12:34.987
If your properties continue
earning at the level

12:34.989 --> 12:37.990
they're at now,
you are golden.

12:37.992 --> 12:46.598
♪♪

12:46.600 --> 12:48.400
Everything go okay
at the house this morning?

12:48.402 --> 12:51.737
Yeah, security's still
on the same shift rotation.

12:51.739 --> 12:53.672
Saw the caterer,
florist.

12:53.674 --> 12:55.207
And another
lighting truck.

12:55.209 --> 12:56.943
Damn, that's the third one.

12:56.945 --> 12:59.678
They're still gonna be doing
the film shoot there?

12:59.680 --> 13:02.615
Yeah.
What happened to your hand?

13:02.617 --> 13:04.517
What happened to your face?
We done?

13:06.554 --> 13:08.754
These two, huh?

13:08.756 --> 13:10.556
Alright, give me a sec.

13:14.963 --> 13:16.762
You smoke?

13:16.764 --> 13:18.831
[ Exhales sharply ]

13:20.568 --> 13:23.435
Is Raj always
that much of a dick?

13:23.437 --> 13:26.372
Mm-hmm.

13:26.374 --> 13:29.241
He shouldn't treat you
like that.

13:29.243 --> 13:30.810
Yeah.
He shouldn't.

13:33.714 --> 13:35.748
Is everything okay?

13:37.385 --> 13:39.718
Noah's back.

13:39.720 --> 13:41.587
He got special leave
and decided to, uh,

13:41.589 --> 13:43.455
surprise me
for a few days.

13:43.457 --> 13:48.727
Thank God I made it home before
he got there this morning.

13:48.729 --> 13:50.196
Do you think he knows?

13:50.198 --> 13:51.764
No.

13:53.001 --> 13:59.005
I think I need to take a step
back from whatever this is.

14:01.609 --> 14:05.611
I knew
that you were married.

14:05.613 --> 14:06.945
I'm gonna get someone else to

14:06.947 --> 14:10.549
take care of
your legal shit here.

14:10.551 --> 14:12.484
Don't call me.

14:12.486 --> 14:17.756
♪♪

14:17.758 --> 14:20.292
What was that?
Nothing.

14:20.294 --> 14:22.828
It doesn't look like nothing.
She's married.

14:22.830 --> 14:25.231
She's got a ring
around her finger.

14:25.233 --> 14:26.632
It's just not a good idea.

14:26.634 --> 14:28.500
I can handle it.

14:28.502 --> 14:33.171
Well, things go wrong, her
husband could come after you.

14:33.173 --> 14:35.574
It could be trouble
for the whole family.

14:35.576 --> 14:37.576
He's not gonna find out.

14:37.578 --> 14:39.712
You don't know that.

14:39.714 --> 14:42.715
There's other women
out there.

14:42.717 --> 14:45.618
Let's go. I gotta get
this septic truck.

14:56.797 --> 14:58.997
Baz:
Safe's in the car.

14:58.999 --> 15:00.332
Any problems?

15:00.334 --> 15:02.801
Nope.
Went off easy.

15:02.803 --> 15:05.671
Hey, Craig, Deran, it's time
to get dressed for dinner.

15:05.673 --> 15:07.473
He's almost been under
for a minute.

15:07.475 --> 15:09.141
Wow.

15:09.143 --> 15:10.809
Come on.

15:10.811 --> 15:12.545
You want pie or not?

15:14.482 --> 15:16.282
Hey!

15:16.284 --> 15:17.917
There's pie.

15:28.562 --> 15:31.297
You ready to tell me what
the hell happened back there?

15:31.299 --> 15:32.899
What?

15:32.901 --> 15:35.167
You said we'd be clear
for two hours.

15:35.169 --> 15:37.836
I'd never seen
that guy before.

15:37.838 --> 15:40.238
You know, if you can't handle
this kiddy shit,

15:40.240 --> 15:43.241
she won't let us do
real jobs.

15:43.243 --> 15:44.810
I don't care.

15:47.115 --> 15:48.847
You know, she was never gonna
let you stay in that

15:48.849 --> 15:51.917
Bible study, right?

15:51.919 --> 15:53.385
He didn't deserve it.

15:53.387 --> 15:55.521
A lot of people get dealt crap
they don't deserve.

15:55.523 --> 15:57.123
Doesn't make it right.

15:57.125 --> 15:58.791
Oh, you spend two weeks hanging
with those church freaks,

15:58.793 --> 16:00.793
and now you think
you know what's right?

16:04.865 --> 16:07.133
[ Sighs ]

16:12.006 --> 16:13.539
Smurf:
Come on, boys.

16:13.541 --> 16:16.809
Come and eat.

16:16.811 --> 16:18.276
You must be hungry.

16:18.278 --> 16:19.846
Yeah.

16:28.422 --> 16:31.357
Ugh.
Caught in the act.

16:31.359 --> 16:32.825
It stinks.

16:32.827 --> 16:35.962
[ Pipes rattle ]
Hey, sorry.

16:35.964 --> 16:37.429
I thought I could get you
a clean one,

16:37.431 --> 16:39.832
but my boss made me
do this site today.

16:39.834 --> 16:40.967
Ah, you're all good.

16:40.969 --> 16:43.302
Still good to give it back on,
uh, Saturday?

16:43.304 --> 16:44.570
It's my next shift.

16:44.572 --> 16:46.539
You got it.

16:49.644 --> 16:51.644
So, how you been, man?

16:51.646 --> 16:55.047
I saw they tore down
your mom's old place.

16:55.049 --> 16:56.649
Oh, yeah?
Yeah, it'll probably be,

16:56.651 --> 16:59.652
you know, million dollar
condos by next week.

17:02.790 --> 17:06.659
Good.
Place was a shithole anyway.

17:06.661 --> 17:09.327
Thanks for this.

17:09.329 --> 17:11.730
Hey, you know, if you're
having septic issues,

17:11.732 --> 17:15.201
I can get you a deal.
Nah, I'm all good.

17:15.203 --> 17:17.870
I just need it
for a couple of days.

17:17.872 --> 17:26.144
♪♪

17:26.146 --> 17:34.353
♪♪

17:34.355 --> 17:35.621
[ Cellphone buzzes ]

17:35.623 --> 17:37.623
[ Clanks ]

17:37.625 --> 17:44.697
♪♪

17:44.699 --> 17:51.704
♪♪

17:51.706 --> 17:58.777
♪♪

17:58.779 --> 18:01.780
Yeah?

18:01.782 --> 18:06.652
No, there's a first-aid kit
by the ramp.

18:06.654 --> 18:10.188
What?
Yeah, no --

18:10.190 --> 18:12.991
Okay, just -- just wrap --
wrap it in something.

18:12.993 --> 18:14.993
I'm on my way.

18:14.995 --> 18:16.462
God damn it.

18:16.464 --> 18:22.268
♪♪

18:22.270 --> 18:28.140
♪♪

18:28.142 --> 18:32.210
Who're you?
Detective Thompson.
Nice to meet you.

18:32.212 --> 18:34.280
Well, I don't talk
to cops, so...

18:34.282 --> 18:35.681
Sure you do, Vin.

18:35.683 --> 18:41.487
As long as Phil doesn't find out
you rolled on him, you're good.

18:41.489 --> 18:43.555
All that shit was supposed
to be confidential.

18:43.557 --> 18:45.357
I know, right?

18:45.359 --> 18:46.625
Please.

18:46.627 --> 18:50.296
[ Sniffs ]

18:50.298 --> 18:52.965
[ Sighs ]

18:52.967 --> 18:54.100
What do you want?

18:54.102 --> 18:57.236
What do you remember
about Andrew Cody?

18:57.238 --> 19:00.172
Pope.

19:00.174 --> 19:03.442
From what I understand,
you two were very close.

19:03.444 --> 19:04.577
Yeah.

19:04.579 --> 19:06.445
As close as you can get
to a guy like that.

19:06.447 --> 19:08.247
You were the only cellmate
that lasted more

19:08.249 --> 19:11.717
than a week with him.
So?

19:11.719 --> 19:14.921
So, did he ever mention a woman
named Catherine Belen?

19:17.592 --> 19:19.591
Catherine?

19:19.593 --> 19:22.060
Yeah, he never stopped
talking about her.

19:22.062 --> 19:23.996
Really?
Mm-hmm.

19:23.998 --> 19:27.199
Yeah, he said
she was his wife.

19:27.201 --> 19:30.869
Found out she wasn't his,
that she was his brother's.

19:30.871 --> 19:32.905
Didn't seem to know
the difference.

19:35.409 --> 19:38.344
Couldn't wait to get out,
get back to her.

19:38.346 --> 19:41.948
♪♪

19:45.619 --> 19:53.158
[ Tires screech ]
[ Turns off engine ]

19:53.160 --> 19:54.493
Ah, shit.
Look, I-I told him
not to call you.

19:54.495 --> 19:56.095
I'm not liable
for this shit, man.

19:56.097 --> 19:57.897
I'm not gonna sue anyone.
I'm not gonna sue anyone.

19:57.899 --> 20:04.636
Let me see it.

20:04.638 --> 20:06.706
[ Grimaces ]

20:06.708 --> 20:08.774
Holy shit.

20:08.776 --> 20:10.442
What happened?

20:10.444 --> 20:12.644
Caught it on some the coping
hanging off the end of the ramp.

20:12.646 --> 20:14.914
I told you to
take care of that!
Look, it's fine.
I'll just --

20:14.916 --> 20:16.248
You shouldn't be up
on the coping!

20:16.250 --> 20:17.583
You can't even drop in yet!

20:17.585 --> 20:19.651
[ Stammers ] I'll just take some
Advil or some shit.

20:19.653 --> 20:23.522
Aah! [ Inhales sharply ]
Don't move.

20:23.524 --> 20:26.792
You're moving!
That freaking hurts!

20:26.794 --> 20:28.127
Let's go.

20:28.129 --> 20:29.995
Wait, where?

20:29.997 --> 20:31.663
The hospital.
Come on.

20:31.665 --> 20:34.534
Bro, I don't have money
for the ER, man.

20:34.536 --> 20:36.335
I'll take care of it.

20:40.674 --> 20:46.278
[ Vehicle approaches ]

20:46.280 --> 20:51.617
[ Engine stops ]

20:51.619 --> 20:55.755
I don't think I'll ever
get used to this view, man.

20:55.757 --> 20:58.290
Yeah.

20:58.292 --> 21:00.026
What's going on, man?

21:10.838 --> 21:11.971
What's this for?

21:11.973 --> 21:15.707
Bonus for
the other night.

21:15.709 --> 21:16.908
How's your hand?

21:16.910 --> 21:19.645
It'll be fine.

21:19.647 --> 21:21.781
We did alright.

21:21.783 --> 21:23.915
A couple grand each.

21:23.917 --> 21:25.484
That's nothing, man.

21:27.921 --> 21:29.455
Payday for
a little fun.

21:29.457 --> 21:32.658
Well, it wasn't fun,
though, was it?

21:32.660 --> 21:34.460
It was stupid.

21:34.462 --> 21:35.727
What, do you want to
go to jail

21:35.729 --> 21:38.397
for ripping off
some trucker guy?

21:38.399 --> 21:39.932
Ain't that the point?
What?

21:39.934 --> 21:41.333
Would you still be
stealing shit

21:41.335 --> 21:42.868
if there was no chance
of you getting caught?

21:42.870 --> 21:45.271
The point is to keep the chances
as close to zero as possible,

21:45.273 --> 21:47.406
man, not daring
the cops to show up.

21:53.080 --> 21:54.746
Look, I appreciate
the gesture and all,

21:54.748 --> 22:00.085
but whatever you're planning
next, you can count me out.

22:00.087 --> 22:06.492
[ Birds call,
waves crashing ]

22:16.970 --> 22:19.371
Hi. I'm, uh, looking for the
owner of the property.

22:19.373 --> 22:21.373
A, uh, Brock Fellows?

22:21.375 --> 22:23.442
Is he here?
And you are?

22:23.444 --> 22:25.444
Uh, I'm Eric Barnes.
I'm with the LAFD.

22:25.446 --> 22:28.514
Uh, is it okay if I speak
with him a sec?

22:28.516 --> 22:30.115
Okay.

22:30.318 --> 22:35.855
[ Sensor squealing ]

22:35.857 --> 22:37.923
Cellphone stays outside.

22:37.925 --> 22:40.125
It's, uh -- It's a work phone.
I kinda need it.

22:40.127 --> 22:42.061
No phone, no entry.

22:42.063 --> 22:44.997
Okay.
Well, try a no entry, no party.

22:44.999 --> 22:46.532
What?
Unless you could, uh,

22:46.534 --> 22:53.339
show me the permits
to this event right now.

22:53.341 --> 22:54.606
[ Radio beeps ]

22:54.608 --> 22:57.543
I'm gonna need
you at the gate, Hannah.

22:57.545 --> 22:59.144
Hannah:
So, what's going on?

22:59.146 --> 23:01.681
So, we received
a complaint, uh,

23:01.683 --> 23:04.950
about some code violations
for an event at this property.

23:04.952 --> 23:07.152
Violation?
Wait, for what?

23:07.154 --> 23:08.820
So, some neighbors said
they saw

23:08.822 --> 23:10.489
a couple generators
being unloaded,

23:10.491 --> 23:13.559
and those Fresnels --
not exactly decorative.

23:13.561 --> 23:15.027
You guys doing a film
shoot around here?

23:15.029 --> 23:18.497
Uh, I don't see what that
has to do with you.

23:18.499 --> 23:22.101
Well, it does if you don't
have your permits.

23:22.103 --> 23:24.504
We've never needed
permits before.

23:24.506 --> 23:26.438
Well, you have.
You just, uh --

23:26.440 --> 23:28.173
Well, you were
lucky enough to not,

23:28.175 --> 23:30.042
uh, get a visit
from someone like me.

23:30.044 --> 23:31.310
So...
Well...

23:31.312 --> 23:32.912
No permits, huh?

23:32.914 --> 23:36.048
No.

23:36.050 --> 23:37.649
[ Whistles ]
Alright.

23:37.651 --> 23:39.651
Uh, when is this party
happening?

23:39.653 --> 23:41.653
It's Friday.

23:41.655 --> 23:43.589
Yeah, no, you're gonna have
to push it at least a week.

23:43.591 --> 23:45.057
We can't.
Maybe two weeks.

23:45.059 --> 23:46.392
I mean,
We -- We -- We --

23:46.394 --> 23:47.659
Just until all the filing
gets done, so...

23:47.661 --> 23:49.194
We -- We really can't.
Here's what I can do.

23:49.196 --> 23:51.063
I can get the, uh,
process started

23:51.065 --> 23:53.465
as soon as possible,
okay?

23:53.467 --> 23:55.401
There's, uh --
You got no service here?

23:55.403 --> 23:56.602
Well, it's a jammer.

23:56.604 --> 23:58.003
There's high traffic
with all the prep,

23:58.005 --> 24:01.206
and Brock's
a very<i> private</i> person.

24:01.208 --> 24:04.644
Right. Okay.
Look, we can't cancel.

24:06.948 --> 24:09.881
Please.

24:09.883 --> 24:13.218
Ah.

24:13.220 --> 24:14.820
Okay, let me see
what I can do.

24:14.822 --> 24:18.558
Uh, I still have to cite you for
the, uh, permit violation, okay?

24:18.560 --> 24:19.825
Mm-hmm.
I can't change that.

24:19.827 --> 24:21.893
But maybe --
let me check my schedule,

24:21.895 --> 24:26.031
a-and if I can be here
the day of,

24:26.033 --> 24:27.633
I can make sure everything
proceeds safely.

24:27.635 --> 24:30.369
Okay, how's that?
You mean during the party?

24:30.371 --> 24:32.104
Yes.
I will have to be here.

24:32.106 --> 24:36.242
It's the only way this
is gonna happen, so...

24:36.244 --> 24:37.709
Okay, fine.

24:37.711 --> 24:39.712
But do you --
do you have to wear<i> that?</i>

24:56.730 --> 24:57.663
Hey.

24:57.665 --> 25:01.801
We're gonna go to
Old Man's.

25:01.803 --> 25:03.068
Build a bonfire.

25:03.070 --> 25:04.470
Take tequila shots.

25:04.472 --> 25:07.473
Eh, Andrew's not interested
in our sinful ways.

25:07.475 --> 25:09.509
We're living with
Pope Andrew now.

25:11.412 --> 25:12.612
[ Clatters ]

25:12.614 --> 25:14.914
Come on.
It'd be good to get out of here.

25:24.091 --> 25:25.825
[ Safe box clanging ]

25:25.827 --> 25:28.194
Baz: That's it?
Bring it here, baby.

25:30.164 --> 25:31.697
Come on.

25:31.699 --> 25:37.703
♪♪

25:37.705 --> 25:43.643
♪♪

25:43.645 --> 25:45.244
It's leather.

25:45.246 --> 25:54.986
♪♪

25:54.988 --> 25:56.856
1886.

25:56.858 --> 25:58.558
That's nice.

26:00.662 --> 26:03.595
Well, you're the religious
one now.

26:03.597 --> 26:05.464
What do you think
we can get for it?

26:05.466 --> 26:11.537
♪♪

26:11.539 --> 26:14.073
I think he needs stitches.

26:14.075 --> 26:16.008
Okay.
What's your name?

26:16.010 --> 26:17.943
Uh, Taylor.

26:17.945 --> 26:19.945
And ID, please.

26:19.947 --> 26:22.214
No.

26:22.216 --> 26:24.149
I don't have one.

26:24.151 --> 26:25.351
Okay.
Are you insured?

26:25.353 --> 26:27.353
I'll pay for it.

26:27.355 --> 26:28.954
Fill out what you can here,

26:28.956 --> 26:31.324
and we'll take you back
as soon as we can.

26:37.164 --> 26:38.731
Okay.

26:42.570 --> 26:44.704
Shit.
Hey, let's go, let's go.

26:44.706 --> 26:46.706
Ah. What? Why?
Just come on.

26:46.708 --> 26:48.240
What about my arm?
There's other hospitals.

26:48.242 --> 26:49.441
-Andrew?
-What?

26:49.443 --> 26:51.243
Andrew? Hey.

26:51.245 --> 26:58.117
♪♪

26:58.119 --> 27:01.821
Hi, Amy.

27:05.860 --> 27:08.994
[ Telephone rings distantly ]

27:08.996 --> 27:10.396
I'm gonna finish this.

27:15.603 --> 27:17.670
Who's that?

27:17.672 --> 27:22.475
He's just a kid
from my skate park.

27:22.477 --> 27:25.611
Your skate park?

27:25.613 --> 27:28.747
Yeah, I felt like building
something, s-so I did,

27:28.749 --> 27:33.619
and then these kids
just all started showing up.

27:33.621 --> 27:35.020
It's just a few ramps.

27:35.022 --> 27:36.889
I mean, it's --
it's not a big deal.

27:36.891 --> 27:38.558
That's great.

27:42.497 --> 27:44.763
Are you sick?

27:44.765 --> 27:46.631
Oh.
Uh, no.

27:46.633 --> 27:48.701
Uh, another waitress I worked
with sliced her hand,

27:48.703 --> 27:52.505
and I was the only one driving
who had a car, so...

27:52.507 --> 27:55.141
Taylor,
we can see you now.

27:57.845 --> 27:59.778
Wow.

27:59.780 --> 28:01.780
And she'll take your payment
details when you're ready.

28:01.782 --> 28:03.449
C-Cash.

28:08.523 --> 28:10.589
Hey.

28:10.591 --> 28:15.260
That's a good thing
you're doing, with that kid.

28:15.262 --> 28:17.462
[ Scoffs ]
I don't know about that.

28:17.464 --> 28:20.199
Got a pretty big hole
in his arm.

28:20.201 --> 28:21.934
Amy, we can go.
Okay.

28:21.936 --> 28:27.540
Um, it was good to see you,
Andrew.

28:27.542 --> 28:29.008
Yeah, you, too.

28:29.010 --> 28:35.014
♪♪

28:35.016 --> 28:41.287
♪♪

28:47.762 --> 28:50.095
What's up?

28:50.097 --> 28:53.098
Uh, just here to grab
my Thunderbolt.

28:53.100 --> 28:55.300
Oh, yeah?

28:55.302 --> 28:57.036
Well, it's not here.

28:57.038 --> 28:59.171
It's at my house.

28:59.173 --> 29:00.839
Why?
You been using it?

29:00.841 --> 29:02.375
No.

29:02.377 --> 29:06.178
Just been sitting there for the
past six months collecting dust.

29:06.180 --> 29:08.113
Thought you forgot about it.

29:08.115 --> 29:11.384
Yep.
Well, I didn't.

29:13.788 --> 29:16.188
You gonna tell me what
really happened to your hand?

29:16.190 --> 29:17.990
Why do you give a shit?

29:19.794 --> 29:24.397
Well, because we're heading
into a job,

29:24.399 --> 29:26.399
and you've been acting
all shady and shit.

29:26.401 --> 29:28.267
I just...

29:28.269 --> 29:31.270
I want to know
what's going on.

29:31.272 --> 29:33.806
So, what? Now, you wanna be
my babysitter and shit?

29:33.808 --> 29:35.074
No.

29:35.076 --> 29:36.742
I-I-I'm flying blind
into this house,

29:36.744 --> 29:40.345
and I need to know that you have
my back outside. That's all.

29:40.347 --> 29:41.680
What are you
talking about, man?

29:41.682 --> 29:43.416
Look, even if I get into
this house with the phone,

29:43.418 --> 29:45.017
they can jam
the signal, okay?

29:45.019 --> 29:46.752
The timing has got to be
just right.

29:46.754 --> 29:48.087
Great.

29:48.089 --> 29:49.755
You know, they've already got
a shit-ton of paparazzi

29:49.757 --> 29:51.957
and a tour bus that goes
by there every 10 minutes.

29:51.959 --> 29:53.626
So?

29:53.628 --> 29:55.560
So, you get made, we're all
already in about 100 pictures

29:55.562 --> 29:57.696
that the paparazzi
have taken of us outside.

29:57.698 --> 30:00.032
That's what you're
worried about.

30:00.034 --> 30:01.634
Alright.

30:01.636 --> 30:03.035
Yeah.

30:03.037 --> 30:11.043
♪♪

30:11.045 --> 30:18.984
♪♪

30:18.986 --> 30:22.387
Hey.

30:22.389 --> 30:25.390
What?
You screening my calls now?

30:25.392 --> 30:28.593
Sorry. I should've
gotten back to you.

30:28.595 --> 30:31.063
Well, I just figured
I'd make sure you were alive

30:31.065 --> 30:33.266
before I went back to LA.

30:33.268 --> 30:35.368
Yeah, well,
we've been swamped.

30:38.205 --> 30:41.474
Well, I upgraded
to a corner suite, so...

30:43.544 --> 30:45.478
At least
you could have called.

30:45.480 --> 30:47.213
I'm sorry.

30:49.550 --> 30:53.018
Are you?

30:53.020 --> 30:54.687
We've just been real busy.

30:54.689 --> 30:57.422
Mm.

30:57.424 --> 31:00.159
Is that it?

31:00.161 --> 31:01.761
Is it a job?

31:04.499 --> 31:06.632
Um, no.

31:06.634 --> 31:09.902
I, um --
I've been seeing someone,

31:09.904 --> 31:11.971
and I guess I should have
told you that, right?

31:11.973 --> 31:20.646
But I didn't mean for it to turn
into anything, but it has.

31:20.648 --> 31:22.781
Hmm.

31:22.783 --> 31:24.483
So, it's real, huh?

31:28.055 --> 31:30.789
Does she even know
what you do?

31:30.791 --> 31:32.124
What do you mean?
I don't know.

31:32.126 --> 31:35.127
What version of you
is she getting?

31:35.129 --> 31:38.331
What,
the clean-cut college boy?

31:38.333 --> 31:42.467
Or maybe just a-a hint of the
underprivileged kid sob story?

31:42.469 --> 31:45.070
I don't --
I don't know which one.

31:45.072 --> 31:46.739
You don't know me.

31:46.741 --> 31:48.341
Yeah.

31:48.343 --> 31:50.075
That much is clear.

31:50.077 --> 31:53.346
♪♪

31:53.348 --> 31:55.348
[ Door opens ]

31:57.418 --> 31:59.318
♪ I got a feeling ♪

32:01.488 --> 32:04.223
Yo, we don't open up
for another half hour.

32:04.225 --> 32:06.425
Oh, we're not here to drink.

32:06.427 --> 32:08.227
We just bought the place
down the street.

32:08.229 --> 32:11.364
It used to be, uh,
Sun of a Beach.

32:11.366 --> 32:13.499
Parker was desperate
to unload it.

32:16.904 --> 32:19.638
He told us about the supply
issues, broken windows,

32:19.640 --> 32:24.243
said somebody pissed
in his tequila bottles?

32:24.245 --> 32:29.314
Yeah, it's hard to open up a
business down here in Oceanside.

32:29.316 --> 32:31.250
We want to work out a deal.

32:31.252 --> 32:32.585
To get off
on the right foot.

32:32.587 --> 32:37.256
We cut you in, we don't have
to worry about any...

32:37.258 --> 32:39.158
incidents.

32:41.396 --> 32:43.863
Three percent.

32:43.865 --> 32:45.664
It won't be much at first,

32:45.666 --> 32:48.667
but the first place
we opened back in the OC,

32:48.669 --> 32:52.204
we pulled in a few hundred grand
in our second year.

32:52.206 --> 32:57.743
Wow.

32:57.745 --> 33:01.680
Okay. Well, take a few days
to think it over.

33:01.682 --> 33:03.583
You know where
to find us.

33:15.162 --> 33:16.729
Okay.

33:20.301 --> 33:22.034
[ Door opens ]

33:22.036 --> 33:30.309
♪♪

33:30.311 --> 33:38.784
♪♪

33:38.786 --> 33:47.126
♪♪

33:47.128 --> 33:55.400
♪♪

33:55.402 --> 33:56.936
Andrew?

33:58.939 --> 34:00.773
Somebody broke into
the rectory.

34:03.744 --> 34:05.745
Was it you?

34:07.682 --> 34:09.548
[ Grunts ]
Gah! Andrew!

34:09.550 --> 34:12.217
[ Panting ]

34:12.219 --> 34:13.886
Jesus forgives you.

34:13.888 --> 34:15.220
No!

34:15.222 --> 34:16.789
Andrew.

34:19.226 --> 34:20.293
Jesus forgives you.

34:20.295 --> 34:21.960
[ Grunts ]

34:21.962 --> 34:26.565
[ Panting ]

34:26.567 --> 34:29.368
Jesus forgives you.

34:29.370 --> 34:32.838
Jesus forgives you!

34:32.840 --> 34:34.640
Andrew!

34:38.045 --> 34:42.982
♪♪

34:42.984 --> 34:44.183
Yo.
Hey.

34:44.185 --> 34:49.388
Can I get a beer?
Yeah.

34:49.390 --> 34:51.056
How'd it go with
the assistant?

34:51.058 --> 34:53.125
It went well.
I'm in.

34:53.127 --> 35:02.335
I got something I gotta talk
to you about.

35:06.874 --> 35:08.273
What's up?

35:08.275 --> 35:09.875
There's some new owners
that took over and bought,

35:09.877 --> 35:15.480
uh, Sun of a Beach.

35:15.482 --> 35:18.217
[ Exhales sharply ]
Okay?

35:18.219 --> 35:22.421
They, uh, came by here,
trying to cut me in

35:22.423 --> 35:25.024
as long as we don't
give them any shit.

35:25.026 --> 35:27.092
They want to pay us
to leave them alone?

35:27.094 --> 35:30.229
Something like that,
yeah.

35:30.231 --> 35:32.231
Well,
how much did they offer?

35:32.233 --> 35:35.234
Three percent.

35:35.236 --> 35:37.103
We should be able
to get that up.

35:38.639 --> 35:39.905
[ Sighs ]

35:39.907 --> 35:41.774
You sure you really want
to keep dealing with all this

35:41.776 --> 35:44.309
LA bar bullshit?

35:44.311 --> 35:47.179
Doesn't matter.
It's all bullshit.

35:47.181 --> 35:48.847
The point is they came
to us first.

35:48.849 --> 35:50.315
That's what we want.

35:50.317 --> 35:53.252
Yeah, and what if this shit
kills my business?

35:53.254 --> 35:55.988
What's your margin right now?
4%? 5%?

35:55.990 --> 35:58.457
Something like that,
yeah.

35:58.459 --> 36:00.626
Get your cut up to 5,
and you're covered.

36:01.328 --> 36:05.398
[ Scoffs ]
Alright.

36:05.400 --> 36:07.132
I'll set up
a meeting with them.

36:07.134 --> 36:15.474
♪♪

36:15.476 --> 36:23.416
♪♪

36:23.418 --> 36:31.556
